SIMPLE: natal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Natal
<hw>Na"tal</hw> <pr>(n⟦amac⟧"t⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>natalis</ets>, fr. <ets>natus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>nasci</ets> to
be born: cf. F. <ets>natal</ets>. See <er>Nation</er>, and cf.
<er>Noel</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to one's birth;
accompanying or dating from one's birth; native.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Princes' children took names from their <qex>natal</qex>
places.</q> <rj><qau>Camden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Propitious star, whose sacred power⟦br⟧
Presided o'er the monarch's <qex>natal</qex> hour.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astrol.)</fld> <def>Presiding over nativity;
<as>as, <ex>natal</ex> Jove</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Native, natural. See <er>Native</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Natal boil</ent>⟦br⟧
